    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ bounds remain within clinical hemolysis thresholds at 4 of 5 operating points and the PIV velocity comparison demonstrates adequate flow-field fidelity. The discretization error factor gap (GCI not formally documented) and the missing hemolysis validation coverage at two operating points are noted as residual uncertainties. The declared mesh independence verification activity provides procedural assurance even though the corresponding GCI evidence artifact has not been formally linked. Overall risk posture judged acceptable under the Low assurance level classification with acknowledgment of the identified gaps.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
